readme:
## unix-cat unix-cat == console.log
cat() is less work than console.log()
this one is for the lazy cats ### installation npm install unix-cat ### usage ```javascript cat('hello world'); // hello world cat([1,2,3]); // [1,2,3] cat({key:'value'}); // {key:'value'} cat(12345); // 12345 cat(1.2345); // 1.2345 ```
